\b0 Robert Benchley is a student at the Coastal School (\'93Coastal\'94) with a history of violent behavior. Problem, p. 7. Defendant Dr. Catherine Becker is a psychologist whom Robert\'92s parents hired to treat him while at Coastal. 
\i Id. 
\i0 Coastal\'92s staff psychotherapist had been treating Robert until he warned the school\'92s principal about threats Robert made against other students during therapy. File, p. 10. Robert reacted poorly to what he saw as a breach of trust and only agreed to stay at Coastal if Defendant would be his therapist. 
\i Id.
\i0 \
Coastal is a special boarding school for children with behavioral problems. Problem, p. 7
\i .
\i0  Since enrollment is voluntary and there are no guards on campus, it is not a detention center of any kind. 
\i Id.
\i0  However, students are not allowed to leave campus without permission and may be punished for doing so. 
\i Id.\

